name: Macadam Building, Strand Campus, Kings College London
directions: Go through the main (glass) doors to the KCLSU building, immediately on the right there are 2 gender neutral single stall bathrooms and 1 gender neutral wheelchair accesible toilet
comment: Normally just walk in and there should be no problems. On busy evenings (Thursday and Fridays after 7ish) there may be someone checking college ID cards inside, I think they will let you use the bathroom if you make it clear you aren't trying to get to the SU Bar.

name: Target
directions: Front of store, to direct left after entering. If you pass the Starbucks, you've gone too far.
comment: I've worked at this Target, during which time I was out as trans, and received verbal confirmation by my supervisors that their restrooms are trans-safe.

name: Arsha Vidhya Gurukulam
directions: In the main temple hall, to the left of the main prayer room.
comment: There are three, clean, unisex bathrooms. This is part of an open Hindu temple and both community and staff is very accepting of all individuals. There are free meals after daily routine prayers that are open to anyone.

name: Allegheny College Pelletier Library
directions: first floor
comment: Staff may be wary of individuals who do not look like college students

name: The Lighthouse Pub
directions: To the right of the main indoor bar/dining area, there are signs. There is an ramp to the bar next to the carpark.

name: Starbucks
directions: Alcove to the left.
comment: You don't need to be a paid customer.

name: Trader Joe's
directions: Back of the store directly parallel to the entrance. Next to the fresh foods counter.

name: Ballard Market
directions: Back of the store
comment: 24 hour store

name: Ann Arbor hands on museum
directions: Basement single stall
comment: You have to be a visitor to the museum

name: Shell Timewise
directions: Inside to the right
comment: The bathrooms are labeled for male or female but the employees are all extremely supportive of safe spaces and you can use whichever restroom you want without worrying about anything.

name: T. A. Blakelock Highschool
directions: Located at the end of the Upper East hallway (2nd floor and to the left), beside the windows.

name: Tufts CLIC building
directions: First floor in the middle of the long hallway, for on the left
comment:
Building is open and unlocked Monday-Friday 9-5
Bathroom also has a changing station

name: Five Guys
directions: Back right of store floor
comment: Usually busy enough to just walk in, I'm a former employee and have never seen any questioned when walking straight into the restroom

name: Alderman hall
directions: On the first floor (so you will have to go downstairs if you go in through the main entrance on the third floor) next to the men's room

name: Peggy Notebaert Nature Museum
directions: Third floor by the bird walk entrance, by elevator.
comment: You have to be a paying customer.

name: Emissary
comment: Right by registers so probably buy a coffee or something to go

name: Starbucks
directions: Around the back of the little stand where they sell the mugs and such, there are two single unisex restrooms.

name: Asbury Woods Nature Center
directions: In the immediate entryway, directly to the left.
comment: Hours can be weird and seasonal so your best bet is checking their site. It's listed at the bottom left. http://www.asburywoods.org/visit-asbury-woods/nature-center-1

name: The Forest Cafe
directions: Down the stairs and through the art gallery bit
comment: Best to buy something first but the entire cafe is a safe space for everyone

name: Nordhoff High School
directions: Go into the office, to the left, inside nurse's office
comment: Sign states it's just for faculty so get office permission to use first

name: Home depot
directions: Left side wall, next to the lumber. Family bathroom next to the men and women bathrooms.

name: WFCU
directions: Two family bathrooms by the recreation pool

name: Merry Maids
directions: Back of hall by water cooler
comment: Can use, just act like you're in a hurry

name: Glasgow Disability benefits centre
directions: Ground floor
comment: Available for patients/claiments and family who have an appointment.

name: University zavits hall
directions: Second floor across from office

name: University centre
directions: Second floor

name: Home Drpot
directions: Very back of stoor first restroom.

name: James B Hunt Jr. Centennial Campus Library
street: James B Hunt Jr. Centennial Campus Library
directions: 1203, bottom floor next to the elevators

name: Fresh west pizza
comment: It's a restaurant so you need to get something to eat, but they have pizzas that fit almost all diet restrictions including vegan and gluten free.

name: Fresh west pizza
comment: It's a restaurant so you need to get something to eat, but they have pizzas that fit almost all diet restrictions including vegan and gluten free.

name: swah-rey
directions: Walk straight to the back where the glass bubble chandelier is, then they are on your right.
comment: They really prefer if you buy something, but they have $1 mini cakes that you can take to go so it's really easy to accommodate for that.

name: Hampton Inn
directions: In the lobby.  Past the water fountains.

name: Epiphany Episcopal Church
directions: Two bathrooms off the hall from parking lot in the back.

name: Florida Institute of Technology, All Faiths Center
directions: Walk in and turn left, down a hallway. There are two different bathrooms on the left; both are gendered, but they're single stalls. If you need help finding it, there are plenty of people to ask.
comment: This building IS used for religious services, typically Christian ones, so if people are there just be quiet and respectful.

name: Starbucks
directions: Two gender neutral, accessible restrooms are in the back, past the tables.

name: Starbucks
directions: All the way at the back of the store. Go directly towards the back, past the counter.
comment: You need a pin number. Depending on who's there, you have to buy something. If it's busy enough, though, you can pretty much just ask for the number and they'll give it to you.

name: Dairy Queen
comment: For customers only

name: Publix Food and Pharmacy
directions: When you walk in, look to the right. Go directly down the aisle that the sign points to, the bathrooms are on the left. There are men's, women's, and a family restroom.
comment: I'm an FtM and use this bathroom all the time. No problems. Just act purposeful. If someone's using the family, just act like you're waiting on someone else to come out (i.e. mom or dad, brother, sister or friend) and no one will question you. NOTE: Some employees like to use this bathroom as opposed to the others. They have walked up before, knocked and said they need to go when the store is practically empty and there are obviously plenty of other toilets.

name: Giant Robot Comics
directions: Back behind the figure shelves. Staff is accepting, if you need to ask them.
comment: The staff and management are very welcoming of trans people, extremely kind. No purchase necessary to use the washroom if you're respectful in there.

name: Compass Counseling
directions: Through the front door, turn right down the hallway
comment: Two all-gender accessible single stalls

name: The Tattered Book
directions: In the back, on the right hand side of the store
comment: Store doesn't always keep regular hours

name: Yellow Church Cafe
directions: On the dining floor, behind the staircase to the right.
comment: Only dining customers are allowed to use it, though you can come in, buy a cookie or a cinnamon roll, and use it

name: Walmart
directions: Family bathroom. On the left wall of the store, at Site to Store.
comment: You don't have to buy anything.

name: Shilling Community Center
directions: Shilling Community Center on Kadena AB. Between the two gendered restrooms.
comment: You must have access to Kadena AB to use this restroom.

name: Circle K/Shell Station
directions: On the left by the checkout area
comment: Safe place. No bathroom keys required and the employees won't say anything.

name: U n mart
directions: On outside west wall of bldg unisex  singlenstall locks

name: J.P. Licks, Wellesley, MA
directions: straight back from the door
comment: no key required - if locked then it's occupied, but you can wait & even get ice cream samples! staff may try to take your order but won't mind if you just want to use the bathroom.

name: Regal 8 Cinema
directions: Unisex single-person restroom down hall for theaters 4-8
comment: For customers only

name: Half Price Books
directions: 2 unisex single-person restrooms in back left corner (near world history section)
comment: Store hours 9am-10pm Mon-Sat, 10am-8pm Sun.

name: Kenton County Public Library
directions: First floor, clearly marked. Individual stalls in women's and men's bathrooms.
comment: Family/handicapped single bathroom, ask at circulation desk for it to be unlocked.

name: Olson campus center
directions: Two gender neutral rooms on the second floor near the coffee shop

name: Starbucks
directions: Back of the store, past the exit sign and through the extra seating area. At the end of a short hallway with a few corners.
comment: As far as I know, you don't have to buy anything to use it, but I'm not 100% certain so keep that in mind. There's two single-stall gender neutral restrooms next to each other, so if one is in use there's still a second one available.

name: Starbucks Dulaney Valley
directions: All the way in the back to the left. Two bathrooms.

name: Signature Theatre
directions: Up the spiral light up stairs, past the merchandise tables, and down the hall ro the right
comment: Allows customers to use the bathroom that best corresponds to their gender identity

name: Starbucks Willow Lake
directions: Back of the store

name: Starbucks
directions: On far side from Lake Cook Rd; left bathroom has an infant changing table and right bathroom has a urinal. However, both are strictly gender neutral and many cis customers use both indiscriminately.
comment: You can go in through the back (from the large parking lot) and end up right by the restrooms. This is especially ideal if you want to avoid interacting with baristas or customers as there are few tables in the area.

name: Quaker, Steak & Lube (Valley View)
comment:
Pay in order to use
There's only a women's and men's bathroom, so don't use either if non-binary, transgender, etc.

name: Fenway Target
comment: There are gendered multi stall bathrooms and a single stall accessible "Family " restroom

name: Medgar Evers Pool
directions: 2 single stall unisex bathrooms in enclaves to the right of the front door
comment: Bathrooms being open is dependent on whether facility is open to the public at the time

name: Broadcast Coffee
directions: To the right of the fridge, straight back
comment: You have to be a paying customer

name: O'Connell's Irish Bar
directions: Past the downstairs bar and to the right, middle WC is unisex.
comment: Not sure if this is accessible or not but erred on side of not accessible because I can't remember what the entrance is like and the bar in general is quite narrow so it might not be wide enough for a wheelchair.

name: Lyon College Alphin Building
directions: In the small hallway outside of the gallery room.
comment: It's an open campus, but the building may be locked at later hours.

name: Macy's, Lower Floor
directions: Lower floor, in between shoes and intimate apparel/womens pajamas. Has a sign leading back to it. Next to the mens and womens restrooms. Single occupancy family restroom, locking door, one toilet. Big enough for a wheelchair but does not have railings on the wall.
comment: Source: I work here. You don't have to buy anything or do anything to use this restroom safely, you can go into Macy's just for this. This is usually a very clean restroom and there's not usually a line unless it's very busy. Hope this helps!

name: University of Las Vegas Nevada
street: 4505 S Maryland Pkwy, Las Vegas, NV 89154
directions: First floor of Student Union near the elevators
comment: Next to the regular restrooms

name: Apex Wine and Design
directions: Located in the back of the studio
comment: (For customers; just come in and inquire about classes, prices of private parties, etc, look around the studio -- then I'm sure the studio manager will let you use the restroom!)

name: La Conversation
directions: In the back
comment: Paying customers

name: Hugo's
comment: Full-service restaurant--have to be a paying customer. Two bathrooms, one ladies and one ungendered

name: Cary Wine and Design
directions: Behind a corner in the front studio room.
comment: (Bathroom for customers; come in and ask for information on classes and private parties, browse the paintings, etc. Then the studio manager will be happy to let you use the restroom!)

name: iron spike model train museum
directions: straight back and to the left, three undgendered bathrooms, two with grab rails.
comment: open only on the weekends, free admission for military and dependents, must pay to enter for everyone else (if you ask politely they might let you come in just for the bathroom and a small donation instead)

name: Gamlin Whiskey House
directions: in the back corner, tucked behind the two single stall gendered bathrooms
comment: there are also a single stall male and single stall female, gendered, bathroom.

name: Reynolds High School
directions: Second floor near room 210 and a staircase, next to women's bathrooms.
comment: Have to attend the school or act like it... so probably youth oriented

name: Nema's
directions: Two gender neutral single occupancy restrooms across from the bar before the kitchen.
comment: Friendly staff. Small restaurant.

name: Camden Interlocken
comment: Apartment leasing building, may not allow guests

name: Arenas
directions: In the back by the soda fountain

name: Early bird
comment: Also both with nice changing tables

name: 302 Coffee
directions: Two restrooms: one toward the front, just off the gift shop, and the other one is closer to the back, in the middle of the artist areas. Both are unisex and accessible.

name: Starbucks
directions: The bathrooms are right inside the south side door of the building.

name: Carnegie-Stout Public Library
directions: 2on first floor near check out desk, 2 on second floor near internet computers, 2 on second floor near reference desk, two on third floor near rotunda (take the elevator to third floor)

name: Your Home Public Library
directions: In the hallway between the side entrance and the main library is a single-stall handicap-accessible restroom.

name: Emmanuel Church
directions: To the right of the sanctuary, near the kitchen. No need to go down the stairs. (If coming from the street, use the door to the church nearest to Arlington St to enter the building.) There is a gender neutral bathroom sign on the wall. The bathroom itself has an unmarked wooden door with a lock sign on the outside that will read "engaged" if someone is inside.
comment: Easy access to this restroom on Sunday mornings, and often Saturday mornings if there is an open rehearsal. Other times, the door to the church may be locked, depending on the church's schedule. Friendly progressive church community-- they encourage members to put their pronouns on their name tag to make transgender members feel more welcome.

name: Zoe's Kitchen
directions: Restrooms are to the rear of the restaurant, around behind the drink fountain.
comment: Zoe's Kitchen is a great restaurant with delicious food! (And lots of vegetarian + vegan options.)

name: (Out front of) Haven & Space
directions: Public toilet out front of Haven & Space, just off the main road of Berry. Parking out front.
comment: Jusr regular unisex toilets with accessibility  (flat entrance/slight rise) sink inside stall and large space would fit big wheelchair.

name: Knights Moves Cafe Somerville
directions: In the back room to the right. Not super nice and there is a step up to the toilet, but unisex.
comment: Probably only reasonable to use if you are playing games in the cafe.

name: Starbucks Town Square Wheaton
directions: straight back from the door, one if you keep going forward with a urinal in it, one to the right with no urinal

name: Tio Gordos Cocina
directions: Past opening glass doors

name: Cafe Boba
comment: For paying customers, but they have many $1 items

name: Starbucks
directions: To the left of the order line.
comment: Must be a paying customer

name: Wasabi House
directions: Back right of restaurant, behind curtains.
comment: May need to be a paying customer. Two single-person bathrooms with locking doors, one labeled male and the other female.

name: Al Vento italian restaurant
directions: Just past the bar at the top of the stairs
comment: Should probably be a customer, but a great restaurant if you're planning a night out.
